launch.name: Starlink-28 (v1.0)
launch.details: This mission launches the 28th batch of operational Starlink satellites, which were version 1.0, from SLC-40. It was the 29th Starlink launch overall. The satellites plan to be delivered to low Earth orbit and will spend a few weeks maneuvering to their operational altitude. The booster is expected to land on ASDS JRTI.
